<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF89FF92F551FE8FEAF8FEC5" box="[1095,1224,292,318]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">T. pallidus</emphasis>
(Haliday)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF89FF92F038FEEEEFF4FEA5" box="[302,452,324,351]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStart-3="Fig" captionStart-4="Fig" captionStartId-0="10.[172,205,1714,1736]" captionStartId-1="6.[170,202,1708,1730]" captionStartId-2="7.[174,205,1723,1745]" captionStartId-3="8.[166,199,1774,1796]" captionStartId-4="9.[174,207,1715,1737]" captionTargetBox-0="[256,1150,742,1692]" captionTargetBox-1="[296,1099,565,1690]" captionTargetBox-2="[534,881,1072,1704]" captionTargetBox-3="[470,920,995,1753]" captionTargetBox-4="[284,1144,1000,1650]" captionTargetId-0="figure-11@10.[253,1162,742,1695]" captionTargetId-1="figure-130@6.[288,1111,557,1687]" captionTargetId-2="figure-347@7.[529,894,1061,1710]" captionTargetId-3="figure-11@8.[467,924,992,1761]" captionTargetId-4="figure-283@9.[260,1148,987,1673]" captionTargetPageId-0="10" captionTargetPageId-2="7" captionTargetPageId-3="8" captionTargetPageId-4="9" captionText-0="Fig. 10. Trioxys curvicaudus, ♀ (1–5) and Trioxys pallidus, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — antenna; 2, 7 — forewing; 3, 8 — propodeum; 4, 9 — petiole; 5 a, 5 b, 10 — ovipositor sheath and prongs. Рис. 10. Trioxys curvicaudus, ♀ (1–5) и Trioxys pallidus, ♀ (6–10): 1, 6 — усик; 2, 7 — переднее крыло; 3, 8 — проподеум; 4, 9 — стебелёк; 5 a, 5 b, 10 — створки яйцеклада и пронги." captionText-1="Fig.6. Paralipsis enervis, ♀ (1–7) and Protaphidius wissmannii,♀ (9–12, 14), Ơ (8, 13): 1, 8 — habitus; 2, 9 — head, lateral aspect; 3, 10 — antenna; 4, 11 — forewing; 5, 12 — propodeum; 6, 13 — petiole; 7, 14 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 6. Paralipsis enervis, ♀ (1–7) и Protaphidius wissmannii, ♀ (9–12, 14), Ơ (8, 13): 1, 8 — габитус; 2, 9 — голова, вид сбоку; 3, 10 — усик; 4, 11 — переднее крыло; 5, 12 — проподеум; 6, 13 — стебелёк; 7, 14 — створки яйцеклада." captionText-2="Fig.7. Pauesia abietis, ♀: 1 — antenna; 2 — mesonotum; 3 — forewing; 4 — propodeum; 5 — petiole; 6 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 7. Pauesia abietis, ♀: 1 — усик; 2 — среднеспинка; 3 — переднее крыло; 4 — проподеум; 5 — стебелёк; 6 — створки яйцеклада." captionText-3="Fig. 8. Praon necans, Ơ: 1 — antenna; 2 — forewing; 3 — propodeum; 4 — petiole. Рис. 8. Praon necans, Ơ: 1 — усик; 2 — переднее крыло; 3 — проподеум; 4 — стебелёк." captionText-4="Fig. 9. Toxares deltiger, ♀: 1 — habitus; 2 — antenna; 3 — mesonotum; 4 — mesopleuron; 5 — forewing; 6 — propodeum; 7 — petiole; 8 — ovipositor sheath." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467470" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6467466" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449137" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449139" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449143" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6467470/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6467466/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6449137/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6449139/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/6449143/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">
fig 10, 
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF89FF92F09EFEEEEFF4FEA5" box="[392,452,324,350]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="399">6–10</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), and differs by: 1) stigma is 2.5 as long as wide; 2) narrower central areola on propodeum; 3) short ovipositor sheath with basal part longer or almost equal to apical part; 4) prongs are slightly curved upward in their distal part, with 2 setae on dorsal side.
</paragraph>
